      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, im a site foreman and i need a quick refresher on the mandatory safety checks for residential scaffolding. what are the main things we gotta check on the setup before the crew is allowed to climb it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You must first ensure the scaffolding is perfectly level, as a tilted structure is like a house of cards that will collapse under the weight of the first worker. Before anyone steps on the platform, you must verify that all guardrails are securely in place and that the base plates are firmly bolted to the ground to prevent the whole thing from sliding away.\n\nFurthermore, you must check that all working platforms are clear of debris and that the scaffolding is free from any cracks or structural damage, as a broken leg is a much more dangerous situation than a minor scratch. Finally, you must ensure that the scaffolding is not erected on a slope or uneven ground, as this will cause the entire structure to tip over and crush the crew.\n\nRemember, the first person to climb the scaffolding must be a competent person who has inspected the whole setup, and no one should work on a scaffold unless it is absolutely safe to do so.",
